title: Song Received from the Spirit Women
A Spirit Woman Gives a Name
lyrics_translation: Kakikcasin names me; the spirits

title: The East God Gave Us this Dance
comments: Drum rhythm: continuous eigth-notes, accented on every other note (i.e., every quarter)
lyrics_translation: The east god (sun) who moves across the sky in a day gave this dance to an Indian in a dream

title: Song to the East God
lyrics_translation: East god (sun), you are the greatest god

Dancing Song from the East God (b)
Dancing Song from the East God (c)
Dancing Song from the East God (d)
In Four Days
lyrics_translation: I will be alive only four days

title: Dancing Song from the South God (a)
Dancing Song from the South God (b)

title: Dancing Song from the South God (d)
Dancing Song from the South God (e)
Dancing Song from the South God (f)
My Gay Dress
lyrics_translation: You will dance for me in my gay dress

title: I Offer My Song
lyrics_translation: When I begin this I offer my song, so I may succeed in getting game

title: I Will Find Game
lyrics_translation: I am now going to look for game and am sure that I will find it

title: I Will Get a Buck
lyrics_translation: I am going to get a buck and I will pack him

title: I Will Shoot Him Through the Heart
lyrics_translation: When I am at a buck I will shoot him through the heart

title: My Tapping Stick
lyrics_translation: I am now going to use my tapping stick

title: You Are Struggling
lyrics_translation: Tomorrow, when I am hunting, you will be struggling and I will shoot you through the heart

title: The Slender-legged Animals
lyrics_translation: When hunting I want to see the slender-legged animals

title: Song After the Feast
lyrics_translation: I bring the ewe deer

title: War Bundle Dance Song (a)
lyrics_translation: In the middle of the great lake I went around

title: He Carries the War Bundle
lyrics_translation: He walks and carries it on his back

title: The War Bundle Causes a Fog
I Am Standing On a Cloud
Pigeon's Dream Song
lyrics_translation: Your tribe will come to you to be cured of sickness

title: Dream Song
lyrics_translation: In the heavens a noise like the rustling of the trees

title: Dream Song Concerning the Sun (a)
lyrics_translation: I am the one, traveling

title: Dream Song Concerning the Sun (b)
lyrics_translation: I know the heavens

title: Song of the Thunderers
lyrics_translation: We are coming and will cover the earth

title: Song Concerning the Kinewuk
lyrics_translation: The voice of the kinewuk comes beforet hem announcing their approach

title: Song of the Little Whirlwind
lyrics_translation: The little whirlwind says, "One who whirls with the wind they call me, the spirits"

title: Dream of Buffalo (a)
lyrics_translation: I am the chief of all the animals that walk

title: Dream of Buffalo (b)
lyrics_translation: In the south I stand

title: Song for Working Magic
lyrics_translation: The pipe that I use to do this

title: Juggler's Song (a)
lyrics_translation: I am going home

title: Juggler's Song (b)
lyrics_translation: The inside of my house is full

title: Song During Treatment of the Sick (a)
lyrics_translation: My lodge stands solid. I walk all over the world

title: Song During Treatment of the Sick (b)
Song of the Woodpecker
lyrics_translation: Woodpecker they call me, the spirits. A person may have worms in him

title: Song of the Healing Spirits
lyrics_translation: They are circling around in the sky (preparatory to going away)

title: Healing Song from the Spirit Women (a)
lyrics_translation: I am going into mud turtle's house

title: Healing Song from the Spirit Women (b)
lyrics_translation: The east women help me all night

title: I Use My Medicine to Cure the Sick
lyrics_translation: I use my medicine to cure her

title: I Give You Medicine to Drink
comments: Densmore notates this without meter or barlines, adding there are "No perceptible accents". Also, she writes "Two renditions of the songs were recorded and are uniform in every respect"
lyrics_translation: I will at least try to give you this medicine to drink

title: I Will Drive the Sickness Out of You
I Am Rewarding You
lyrics_translation: The power above said, It is I who am now rewarding you so that you will live to old age

title: The Heavens Help You
lyrics_translation: The heavens speak and help you and others will depend upon you for help

title: Healing Song (b)
comments: Drum rhythm: continuous eigth-notes|Densmore gives the drum tempo as quaver=184bpm

title: Two Sides of the Heavens
lyrics_translation: The two sides of the heavens are coming together

title: Funeral Song (a)
lyrics_translation: A path on which he goes

title: Manabus and the Stone (a)
lyrics_translation: I am going inside

title: Manabus and the Stone (b)
lyrics_translation: I am going into the green-clouds wigwam

title: Manabus Challenges the Underwater Snake
lyrics_translation: Come and swallow me

title: I Will Hide My Bullet
lyrics_translation: I will hide my bullet in the ground so no one can find it
